It is interesting to look at the annual revenue breakdown for 2009: 89.4% is from passenger traffic with just 5.3% from cargo. The remaining 5.3% is from excess baggage charges, charter, engineering and other services.

==Destinations==
{{Main|Pakistan International Airlines destinations}}
[[File:PIA Destinations - Present and Former.jpg|thumb|{{legend|blue|Pakistan}} {{legend|green|Present destinations}} {{legend|gold|Former destinations}}]]
[[File:PIA A310 Dubai, Balochistan Tail.jpg|thumb|A Pakistan International Airlines [[A310]] at [[Dubai International Airport]]]]. 

[[Dubai]] is a major [[focus city]] for the airline with flights to [[Bahawalpur]], [[Dera Ghazi Khan]], [[Faisalabad]], Islamabad, Karachi, Lahore, [[Multan]], [[Peshawar]], [[Quetta]] and [[Sialkot]]

PIA serves 23 domestic destinations and 36 international destinations in 25 countries across Asia, Europe, North America as of September 2009 from its home bases of [[Karachi]], [[Lahore]], [[Islamabad]] and [[Peshawar]].<ref>[http://www.piac.com.pk/PIA_About/domestic.asp Domestic Network]</ref><ref>[http://www.piac.com.pk/PIA_About/intnetwork.asp International Network]</ref>

